result.execSummary:
The defendant Travis T Ranson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Travis T Ranson in court with attorney Linda Jean Schaefer.  Defendant Travis T Ranson in custody.  Joan Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Minute sheet. State amends Ct. 2 to Misdemeanor Bail Jumping as a Repeater, gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters guilty plea to Ct. 1 as charged and amended Ct. 2. Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds pleas made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts pleas, and finds guilty of Ct. 1 as charged and amended Ct. 2.    Court reviews collateral consequences of felony conviction, possible penalties. Defendant must have a DNA sample on file with the State of Wisconsin and pay a DNA surcharge. State/Defense ready to proceed to sentencing without the benefit of a PSI. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.

Defendant Travis T Ranson in court with attorney Linda Jean Schaefer.  Defendant Travis T Ranson in custody.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. Discussion between counsel and court, matter now set for plea and sentencing next week. Bond remains in effect.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for May 17, 2016 at 08:30 am.
from defendant questioning whether his revocation time will run concurrent on his cases.  Copy of letter forwarded to Atty's Korb and Schaefer.
Defense waives reading of Information and enters not guilty plea.  Bond remains as is.

Defendant Travis T Ranson in court with attorney Linda Jean Schaefer.  Defendant Travis T Ranson in custody.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense waives right to Prelim. Court questions defendant on waiver. Court finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver and binds over for trial. Court finds probable cause for bindover.  Status conference scheduled for May 10, 2016 at 03:15 pm.

Defendant Travis T Ranson in court with attorney Linda Jean Schaefer.  Defendant Travis T Ranson in custody.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. Defense waives reading of the complaint, requests a status. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for March 18, 2016 at 03:00 pm.
No contact direct or indirect with B.M.K., dob 3/27/93.   To be fingerprinted and photographed before leaving the Justice Center.

Defendant Travis T Ranson in court, in custody.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Copy of Complaint given to Defendant in Court.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel, right to preliminary hearing. Defendant indicates he's contacted the PD office regarding legal represendation, believes Atty Sara Malcore may be appointed to represent him. Bond set.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for February 29, 2016 at 10:00 am.
